data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Crafting Geocities Page**\n\nI'm starting with a Geocities-style HTML page. The user wants the page in Dutch. My current focus is figuring out the key components for such a page! I must consider the aesthetic preferences for this project.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Exploring Implementation Options**\n\nI've been exploring different implementation options for this Geocities-style HTML page. Should I return the HTML directly, generate a file, or create a visually appealing display? I'm now referencing the provided guidelines: markdown formatting, handling Chart.js, CSV, LaTeX, and images, as well as the instruction for the user's preferred language, which is Dutch in this case. My focus is on the most appropriate method to deliver the HTML.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Defining Page Elements**\n\nI'm now defining the core elements for this Geocities-style webpage. I'm focusing on incorporating classic elements such as animated marquees, the blink tag (CSS animations are key here, since the `<blink>` element is obsolete), and a MIDI music player (or retro audio button). It's going to have a guestbook, flame dividers, hits counter, and webring links as well. I'm also considering the \"under construction\" graphics, using placeholder or animated CSS elements to avoid external dependency, or archive URLs. The goal is to maximize the retro aesthetic!\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Constructing Webpage Structure**\n\nI'm now determining the structure and content. I plan to use `write_file` to create `geocities.html`. I'll present the code in a markdown block, and explain the code in Dutch. I want a title \"Welkom op Arthur's Digitale Ruimte!\", and am brainstorming a starfield background, CSS-animated rotating skull, and flame borders. I'll include a Guestbook (Gastenboek), a counter, \"Under Construction\" signs created with CSS, and links to \"Mijn Coole Vrienden.\"\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Designing Nostalgic Page**\n\nI'm now integrating more details for the nostalgic Geocities page. I've decided to proceed with `write_file` to create `/geocities.html`. I've added a CSS-styled Winamp audio player (brilliant!), webring, and section for \"Mijn Huisdieren\". My focus is on the fonts, rainbow text effects, and the marquee content. I'm focusing on the nostalgic, interactive design.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Adding Retro Elements**\n\nI'm now adding specific retro elements. I'm focusing on \"UNDER CONSTRUCTION\" text within yellow and black diagonal stripes, and creating a \"Webring\" box. I'm also implementing retro badges using CSS boxes with pixelated text, ensuring they are robust. These badges will look perfect and won't ever break! I'm planning to make the CSS now, and include the black background, the \"Comic Sans MS\" font and stars background.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

